WorkItem.Description:
It would probably be useful to be able to get the binary data returned in a variable. E.g.:
 
$myExcelData = $objWriter->save();
 
Then $myExcelData could be used to a) output it to the browser, b) save it to the disk, or c) save it to a database blob, etc.
 
Of course currently a workaround would be:
 
$objWriter->save('temporaryfile.bin');
$myExcelData = file_get_contents('temporaryfile.bin',FILE_BINARY);
